Former President Jacob Zuma is expected to appear at the state capture inquiry on Monday. JOHANNESBURG - Former President Jacob Zuma is expected to appear at the state capture inquiry on Monday. Five days have been set aside for this key witness. READ: How will Zuma respond at state capture inquiry? Several inquiry witnesses have already implicated Zuma in their testimonies. Sensational claims about how he allegedly helped loot government money have been made at the commission. 